text: Mount Suribachi (Japanese: 摺鉢山, Suribachiyama) is a 169-metre (554 feet)-high Mountain on the southwest end of Iwo Jima. It is in the northwestern Pacific Ocean. The government of Japan's Tokyo Metropolis governs it. ==References== == Other websites == * Japan Meteorological Agency * Category:Mountains of Japan Category:Tokyo Metropolis
